Place Vendome
Apr 2024 • Couples
One of the most important squares in Paris, not because of its beauty/architecture, but for its historic significance.

It's a must-visit on your way from Place de la Concorde to Grands Boulevards. That being said, the square itself isn't much more than its obelisk at the center. However, there are plenty of fancy high-end stores all around.

Shop for Jewelry
Jun 2024 • Couples
Great place if you want to buy some jewelry as there are lots of jewelry showrooms here. Also some other high end shopping. Otherwise the square is stone and cold and unpleasant, even though it has Napoleon's column in the center. Always one of Paris' most ritzy areas, but not much fun.

Square
May 2024 • Solo

Now it’s a nice site surrounded by uber luxury brands like LV, Chanel, Cartier, Hublot et al
